Paper: 08073291
Title: Coulomb gauge gluon propagator and the Gribov formula
Authors: G. Burgio and M. Quandt and H. Reinhardt
Abstract: We analyze the lattice SU(2) Yang-Mills theory in Coulomb gauge. We show that the static gluon propagator is multiplicative renormalizable and takes the simple form $D(|\vec{p}|)^{-1}=\sqrt{|\vec{p}|^2+M^4/|\vec{p}|^2}$, proposed by Gribov through heuristic arguments many years ago. We find $M=0.88(1) {\rm GeV} \simeq 2 \sqrt{\sigma}$.
